Brooklyn College (Brooklyn): Looking eastward across the campus and the new buildings, under construction by the Works Progress Administration. The building with the unfinished tower is the Library. The views are from Ave. H, near Ocean Avenue.

Views 1,2,3

P. L. Sperr

text:
Nostrand Ave., west side, south from Ave. H, showing the Scranton and Lehigh Coal Co., at No. 2206 Nostrand Ave. The trees in this view mark the southern boundary of Brooklyn's City College.

July 5, 1937.

P.L. Sperr.

Brooklyn College (Brooklyn): Viewing west, toward the newly erected buildings, from Nostrand Avenue and Avenue H. The building with the steeple is the Library. These grounds were owned by the Flatbush Golf Club.

July 5, 1937
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr
